    <compoundname>GOTO</compoundname>
    <title>GOTO Keyword</title>
    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para><programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">GOTO<sp/>numeric-constant</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para>Transfers control unconditionally to the line with the given <bold>constant line number</bold> in the current program.</para>
<para><blockquote><para>[!WARNING] <bold>Deprecated / discouraged.</bold> <linebreak/>
 Prefer structured flow control and procedures: <ulink url="https://github.com/brainboxdotcc/retro-rocket/wiki/IF"><computeroutput>IF</computeroutput></ulink>, <ulink url="https://github.com/brainboxdotcc/retro-rocket/wiki/WHILE"><computeroutput>WHILE</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>ENDWHILE</computeroutput></ulink>, <ulink url="https://github.com/brainboxdotcc/retro-rocket/wiki/REPEAT"><computeroutput>REPEAT</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>UNTIL</computeroutput></ulink>, <ulink url="https://github.com/brainboxdotcc/retro-rocket/wiki/FOR"><computeroutput>FOR</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>NEXT</computeroutput></ulink>, and <computeroutput>DEF PROC...</computeroutput>/<computeroutput>ENDPROC</computeroutput> with <computeroutput>PROC</computeroutput> calls. </para>
</blockquote><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>The target must be a <bold>numeric constant</bold>; variables or expressions are not allowed.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Jumps may be forward or backward within the <bold>same program</bold>.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Examples</heading>
</para>
<para><bold>Forward jump</bold> <programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">10<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Start&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">20<sp/>GOTO<sp/>100</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">30<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;This<sp/>line<sp/>is<sp/>skipped&quot;</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">100<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Landed<sp/>at<sp/>100&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><bold>Simple loop with GOTO</bold> <programlisting filename=".basic"><codeline><highlight class="normal">10<sp/>I<sp/>=<sp/>1</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">20<sp/>PRINT<sp/>I</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">30<sp/>I<sp/>=<sp/>I<sp/>+<sp/>1</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">40<sp/>IF<sp/>I<sp/>&lt;=<sp/>5<sp/>THEN<sp/>GOTO<sp/>20</highlight></codeline>
<codeline><highlight class="normal">50<sp/>PRINT<sp/>&quot;Done&quot;</highlight></codeline>
</programlisting></para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
<para><heading level="5">Notes</heading>
</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Jumping to a non-existent line raises a runtime error.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Heavy use of <computeroutput>GOTO</computeroutput> quickly reduces readability; use it only for compatibility with legacy code.</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
